IMF mission postpones visit to Ukraine - media

07 Nov 2019

The IMF mission postponed a visit to Ukraine for several weeks.
On Thursday, November 7, writes the League. Finance with reference to own sources.
On October 21, the Cabinet of Ministers announced that the new IMF mission will arrive in Ukraine in two weeks.
According to the staff of the IMF representative office in Ukraine, the exact date of arrival of the mission has not yet been determined.
According to the publication, in Kiev, the mission is going to study the progress of the government on the path of reform. In particular, 10 reforms will be analyzed:

establishing a budget deficit of 2% of GDP required by the IMF (already included in the draft budget);
return of liability for illicit enrichment;
reform of the Deposit Guarantee Fund for individuals;
granting permission to wiretap the NABU and the State Security Bureau (the relevant law has already been adopted);
introduction of independent supervisory boards of state banks;
the unbundling of Naftogaz (the law has been adopted but not yet signed by the president);
introduction of market gas prices (planned by Naftogaz from January 1);
adoption of a land market law;
ensuring the independence of the Antimonopoly Committee;
work of the National Bank in the banking market.

It is noted that the reason for the likely postponement of the visit of the IMF mission may be a rather lenient punishment for illegal enrichment, the law on which was recently adopted by the Verkhovna Rada.
